@NODE Introduction
@TITLE "Perlin À Introduction"


    @{b}Introduction@{ub}


    Perlin is a Perlin noise generator that can save the resulting image to a
    PNG file for later use.

    Perlin uses the original source code provided by Ken Perlin.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements
@TITLE "Perlin À Requirements"


    @{b}Requirements@{ub}


    o MorphOS 2.0 or better

    o Approx 4 MB free RAM

    o a few KB free harddisk space


@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation
@TITLE "Perlin À Installation"


    @{b}Installation@{ub}


    Copy Perlin drawer to a place you like. No installer required.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Startup
@TITLE "Perlin À Startup"


    @{b}Startup@{ub}


    You can start Perlin from Ambient or from the CLI.
 

    @{b}Ambient@{ub}

    Perlin supports all default MUI and Commodity tooltypes.


    @{b}CLI@{ub}

    It has no options. Just start it.


@ENDNODE


@NODE MenuOptions
@TITLE "Perlin À Menu Options"


    @{b}Menu Options@{ub}


    @{b}Perlin@{ub}

        Save Image...
 
            Perlin can save current texture buffer to PNG image. It features
            automatic filename numbering for easy saving of multiple images
            in a row.

            If "Use alpha channel" option is enabled, the texture will be
            stored in the alpha channel of the image.

            Textures can be stored with seamless borders, if the "Create
            seamless border" option is enabled. Perlin will automatically
            double width and height and fill the new space with flipped
            variants of the texture. There might be still visible repetition.

        About...

            Opens the Aboutbox with copyright information and
            credits.

        Quit

            Quits Perlin immediatelly.


    @{b}Settings:@{ub}

        MUI...

            Opens MUI Settings.


@ENDNODE


